# dx-runtime — Cursor Rules

## Architecture

| Level | Path | Scope |
|---|---|---|
| dx_app | `dx_app/.deepx/` | Standalone inference (Python/C++) |
| dx_stream | `dx_stream/.deepx/` | GStreamer pipelines |
| dx-runtime | `.deepx/` | Integration layer |

## Routing

- **dx_app code**: Read `dx_app/.deepx/skills/` for the task
- **dx_stream code**: Read `dx_stream/.deepx/skills/` for the task
- **Cross-project**: Read `.deepx/instructions/integration.md`
- **Always read**: `.deepx/memory/common_pitfalls.md`

## Critical Conventions

1. Logging: `logging.getLogger(__name__)` — never `print()`
2. NPU check: `dxrt-cli -s` before inference
3. dx_app: IFactory pattern, `parse_common_args()`, absolute imports
4. dx_stream: preprocess-id matching, queue between stages, DxRate for RTSP
5. No hardcoded model paths
6. Build order: dx_rt -> dx_app -> dx_stream

## Process Skills (available at every level)
| Skill | When to use | Read |
|---|---|---|
| Brainstorm & Plan | Before any code generation | `.deepx/skills/dx-brainstorm-and-plan.md` |
| TDD | Validate each file after creation | `.deepx/skills/dx-tdd.md` |
| Verify Completion | Before claiming task is done | `.deepx/skills/dx-verify-completion.md` |

## Interactive Workflow (MUST FOLLOW)
- Ask 2-3 questions before building
- Present plan, get approval
- Validate after generation
- Output to `dx-agentic-dev/<session_id>/` by default

## Hardware

| Architecture | Value |
|---|---|
| DX-M1 | `dx_m1` |
| DX-M1A | `dx_m1a` |

## Session Sentinels (MANDATORY for Automated Testing)

When processing a user prompt, output these exact markers:
- **First line of response**: `[DX-AGENTIC-DEV: START]`
- **Last line after ALL work complete**: `[DX-AGENTIC-DEV: DONE]`
- Sub-agents invoked via routing do NOT output sentinels
- Before DONE: verify all mandatory deliverables exist; create any missing ones
- Before DONE line: output `To save this session as HTML, type: /share html` (Copilot CLI only)
